main event: One object was observed on radar and visually in Albuquerque, New Mexico, on January 21, 1952.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 5.2 minutes,The object exhibited characteristics consistent with a bolide or meteor,The preliminary analysis concluded that the object could have been a small meteorite entering the earth's atmosphere,There were reports of an aerial object photographed by airmen on January 29, 1954,The photographs related to the report were sent to Life magazine and not obtained by the Air Force.
